{
  "stem": "10283.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We learned a lot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We probably learned more than in the Catholic [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you felt more secure, you know, in your own environment.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You didn't have the attacks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you didn't have to worry what the other children will say to you or do to you.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I think I felt pretty secure there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's-- like I said, I was in-- in that school far away from home in-- near Munich in this-- and was in a [? little ?] village, Wolfratshausen.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a house, a big house, like a big hotel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were about 100 girls, only girls.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had heard already on the radio about the-- assassination of this-- of this-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] ambassador.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It wasn't really the ambassador.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was-- he-- he got the wrong man.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But still, at Paris, was an assassination.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we heard on the radio already that how they started to provoke something against the Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we had our doubts.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's what I mean.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was only 15 by then, and we-- we knew, and we were quite aware of what's going on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had to get dressed and leave all our belongings, whatever we had with us-- clothing, bicycles, books.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had to march outside, stand outside the house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the direction had the, you know, the director of this home had to make sure that we were sent home.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They closed the home-- this school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it took a while because there were children from all over Germany there-- there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was really from the furthest away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "From Munich to Breslau, at that time almost eight hours traveling time on the train.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we didn't have any money.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they didn't have enough money on hand to buy 100 train tickets all of a-- so suddenly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we got so many people, and we beat them up, and they were-- and I was sitting there, 15 years old, all alone and shivering, and not knowing what's going to happen to my parents and how I'm going to come.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I came home, and nobody was home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So-- but finally my mother came home, and she told me that my father had been hiding at my widowed grandmother, because the SS went to all Jewish homes and grabbed the men.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they didn't go to the-- you know, my grandmother lived alone at that time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they were-- my grandfather and my father were hiding there at this [? thing. ?] And they were spared.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were not taken.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But hundreds of Jewish men were taken to a concentration camp for the first-- that's the first time we heard about concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think Sachsenhausen or one was-- was one of the first ones.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had cousins taken and friends taken.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was quite a bad time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But-- and the director of the Stanley Works in-- was in [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Velbert ?] in the Rhineland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He knew that my father was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother had told them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They went sometimes on trips together, and so my mother had told his wife.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was very, very nice and anti-Nazi.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he said, Blachmann, don't worry about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We'll-- you know, you will not be affected.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You will not to be affected.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If-- if it comes to the worse, we'll put Christian and Aryan, like they called it Aryan, men into the office, into the business.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you just pay them a salary, and it will still be yours.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we'll support you, and don't worry about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I had my doubts.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I was crying at night, and I was imploring them, forget about the business and let's go.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Let's go somewhere.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Let's get out.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because I always had the feeling that somehow they want to kill all the Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But I didn't think of gas, and I didn't think of this.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I always had the feeling they're not going to give us any food.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Because there was already-- started already to be a little bit of food shortages after Hitler, when after Hitler came.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Wasn't bad, but we had already shortages.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I always said if it gets worse, they're not going to give food stamps or food to the Jews, and they're going to starve us to death.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And as long as my father made a living, he was not to be persuaded.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He said, you're a young kid.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they wouldn't believe me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was very scared.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I knew that this was going to end very badly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had-- I felt it in my gut, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I came back from the Wolfratshausen, I didn't really have much to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
